	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, I thought so. Probably because the demo scene became big with the C64 and the C64 was most popular in Europe.<br /><br />I'm still surprised that some demo artists <em>require</em> the system to run on PAL, though.<br /><br />I mean, first of all, that's not a C64. They code their stuff on modern, region-independent PCs and test it on emulators that have NTSC as the default option.<br /><br />So, not only did they consciously alter the default option from the master console version, that 99 % of the games were programmed for, to the localized version of the country they happen to live in.<br />They also decided to use features that only work on their own version and are totally incompatible with the most common version of the console.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


