		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I would never program a game to be incompatible with either version at all.</div><br />I completely agree, releasing an &quot;NES game&quot; that doesn't work on the majority of NES consoles around the world is a very weird thing to do, to say the least.<br /><br />But if it's a demo, it's understandable that someone would want to take advantage of the ridiculously long vblank to do things that would normally be considered impossible on the NES, just for fun, like I said in my edit above.<br /><br />The payback thing was a joke, obviously, but it wouldn't surprise me if someone from a PAL country chose not to do the extra work to support NTSC after getting the short end of the stick for so long.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
