	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />High Hopes is PAL solely because back then I only owned a PAL NES (it's obligatory to run the demo on the real hardware at Assembly, where it competed). There were also no flash carts around when I was working on the demo (PowerPak came out right after) so I used a gutted Bart vs the World cart. Didn't cross my mind to import an NTSC NES + game(s). <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />All that said, even though I do own an NTSC NES nowadays, I might still target PAL NES for a new demo, because nostalgia and the other reasons mentioned so far.<br /><br />(High Hopes doesn't utilize the longer vblank time. As a sidenote, none of the effects use any MMC3 features either, they're all NROM-compatible.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


